comment_regular_data.body:
@luukvbaal Good work. Thank you for digging into the problem and figuring out the workaround.

>  At least I notice no discernible performance hit

I am not sure but the performance overhead may be noticeable if we have hundreds of code lines in one screen (e.g., using a monitor in portrait orientation), it's worth the effort, however. Before we have an option to toggle the digits, this simulation is the the best solution.

[statuscol.nvim](https://github.com/luukvbaal/statuscol.nvim) now supports a "nodigits" foldcolumn through FFI:
```lua
local builtin = require("statuscol.builtin")
require("statuscol").setup({
  segments = {
    { text = { "%s" }, click = "v:lua.ScSa" },
    { text = { builtin.lnumfunc }, click = "v:lua.ScLa", },
    {
      text = { " ", builtin.foldfunc, " " },
      condition = { builtin.not_empty, true, builtin.not_empty },
      click = "v:lua.ScFa"
    },
}

```
